phy==\n{{see also|Timeline of Nagoya#Bibliography}}\n\n*{{cite journal |last1=Benesch |first1=Oleg |title=Castles and the Militarisation of Urban Society in Imperial Japan |journal=Transactions of the Royal Historical Society |date=2018 |volume=28 |pages=107\u2013134 |doi=10.1017/S0080440118000063 |language=en |issn=0080-4401 |url=http://eprints.whiterose.ac.uk/133333/1/Benesch_Castles_and_the_Militarisation_of_Urban_Society_in_Imperial_Japan_TRHS_Accepted_Manuscript.pdf |access-date=2018-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120055147/http://eprints.whiterose.ac.uk/133333/1/Benesch_Castles_and_the_Militarisation_of_Urban_Society_in_Imperial_Japan_TRHS_Accepted_Manuscript.pdf |archive-date=2018-11-20 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Ryfle|first1=Steve|last2=Godziszewski|first2=Ed|title=Ishiro Honda: A Life in Film, from Godzilla to Kurosawa|publisher=Wesleyan University Press|year=2017|isbn=9780819570871|ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Nagoya}}\n{{Americana Poster|year=1920}}\n{{Wikivoyage|Nagoya}}\n* [http://www.city.nagoya.jp/ Nagoya City official website] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://www.city.nagoya.jp/en/index.html Nagoya City official website] \n* [http://www.wikimapia.org/#y=35150000&x=136910000&z=11&l=1&m=a WikiSatellite view of Nagoya at WikiMapia]\n* [http://www.nic-nagoya.or.jp Nagoya International Center]\n* [http://www.nagoya-info.jp/en/ Official Tourism Guide \u2013 Nagoya Travel Guide ]\n{{Navboxes\n|list  =\n{{Nagoya transit}}\n{{Aichi}}\n{{Metropolitan cities of Japan}}\n{{World's most populated urban areas}}\n{{Most populous cities in Japan}}\n{{Largest cities of Japan}}\n{{JPLargestMetros}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Nagoya| ]]\n[[Category:Cities in Aichi Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Japan]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1614]]\n[[Category:Cities designated by government ordinance of Japan]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Largest city in the Ch\u016bbu region 